"Quixmath"

Desc:
    Simple C equation parser and calculation tool.
    Supports basic operators, exponentiation, and parentheses.

Files:
    src/main.c      - Entry point and AST evaluator.
    src/parse.c/.h  - Equation parser, follows PEMDAS.
    src/flags.c/.h  - Flag and argument parsing.
    src/values.h    - Primitive type aliases.

Building:
    $ make

Installing:
    $ sudo make install

Running:
    $ qm [options] "<equation>"
    $ qm h|help|? (for help)

Options:
    fb              Output result in binary.
    fo              Output result in octal.
    fd              Output result in decimal (default).
    fx              Output result in hexadecimal.
    ib              Parse equation numbers as binary.
    io              Parse equation numbers as octal.
    id              Parse equation numbers as decimal (default).
    ix              Parse equation numbers as hexadecimal.
    o <file>        Write output to file instead of stdout.

Operators:
    +  -  *  /  ^

Testing:
    $ make test

